# Changelog

## Unreleased
- Add `run.sh` helper script.
- Support multiple primitives per ANARI geometry (triangle and quad).
- Support `quad` geometry and multiple surfaces in ANARI `world.surface`.
- Support `primitive.index` for ANARI triangle geometry.
- Render ANARI `frame.world` triangle geometry (minimal world/surface/geometry path).
- Make ANARI `renderFrame()` call photon path tracer (replaces gradient).
- Switch ANARI implementation to `anari::DeviceImpl` style (better compatibility with ParaView/tsd).
- Add ANARI MVP device+frame: `photon_anari_render` renders `anari_out.ppm` via `anariRenderFrame()`.
- Add `SceneBuilder` and update `photon_render` to render a 2-quad scene (vertical + ground).
- Add per-triangle albedo (mesh stores `albedo_per_prim`) and render it in `photon_render`.
- Adjust default camera to frame the mesh quad.
- Fix BVH/AABB traversal for coplanar AABBs (tmax==tmin) so mesh intersections work.
- Fix mesh visibility: use front-facing normals and a camera-facing quad scene.
- Render a triangle mesh via BVH traversal (quad scene) in `photon_render` (removed sphere fallback).
- Add triangle mesh + CPU-built BVH scaffolding (not yet used by renderer).
- Add standalone Kokkos path tracer app (`photon_render`) which writes `out.ppm`.
- Build ANARI loadable library (`anari_library_photon`) with correct exported entrypoint and runnable smoke app.
- Add initial ANARI device scaffolding (device factory stub) and wire anari headers into build.
- Update Kokkos to 5.0.1 and patch/disable anari-sdk build+tests to integrate as dependency.
- Add CMake dependency fetching (Kokkos + ANARI-SDK) and basic project options.
- Add initial CMake project skeleton, library, mini app, and basic unit test.
